Loom `web-design` skill — provenance & attribution
===================================================

This skill is original prose written in Loom's own voice. It distills guidance from three public
design skills, all license-reusable with attribution. No source is reproduced wholesale; the design
facts and numeric values it carries are not themselves copyrightable. Credit and license terms below.


1. Impeccable — https://github.com/pbakaus/impeccable
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Copyright: Paul Bakaus and contributors
   Used: the domain reference + deterministic anti-pattern catalogue — typography, color (OKLCH /
   60-30-10 / dangerous combos), spacing & layout, the eight interactive states, the motion duration
   ladder, and the consensus "don'ts" list.

   Per Impeccable's own NOTICE, it builds on prior work that is carried through here transitively:
     - Anthropic's `frontend-design` skill — Apache License 2.0, © 2025 Anthropic PBC.
     - ehmo's `typecraft-guide-skill` — typography additions merged into Impeccable at the author's
       request. Loom's typography guidance is reworded in Loom's own voice (the numeric values are not
       protectable); no ehmo prose is reproduced verbatim.

   Apache-2.0 changes statement: this skill reuses, reorganizes, condenses, generalizes (made
   stack-agnostic), and rewrites the above material; it is not the original work and is not endorsed
   by its authors.


2. taste-skill — https://github.com/Leonxlnx/taste-skill
   License: MIT License
   Copyright: © 2026 Leonxlnx
   Used: the anti-default discipline (avoid the generated look), the brief-inference / "read the room"
   step, and the intent-dials concept. Re-distilled from taste-skill's v2 rewrite ("design-taste-frontend")
   are: the brief → design-system mapping (which official system suits which ecosystem), the redesign
   audit-first protocol (preserve-vs-overhaul, audit brand/IA/SEO before touching, priority-ordered
   modernisation levers, the never-change-silently list), and the expanded production-test anti-pattern
   tells (div-built fake previews, decorative status dots, middle-dot rationing, scroll cues, fake
   version/build stamps, locale strips, duplicate-CTA-intent). Loom adapts the dials to three named levels
   with a restraint-biased default and does not copy taste-skill's 1–10 numerology, its stack/framework
   prescriptions and code skeletons (React/Next/Tailwind/Motion/GSAP, icon-library lists), or its
   aesthetic-variant skills.


3. Emil Kowalski — design-engineering skill — https://emilkowal.ski/skill
   License: MIT License (per owner verification; the MIT grant is stated at the distribution source)
   Copyright: © Emil Kowalski
   Used: the motion/interaction craft layer — the Animation Decision Framework (animate-at-all?
   frequency, never animate keyboard actions), custom easing curves, spring interruptibility,
   component motion techniques (scale-from-0.95, origin-aware popovers, blur-masked crossfades),
   perceived-performance, and the `Before / After / Why` review format.


